## Definition

For $F \in C$ an [[object]] in an [[(âˆž,1)-category]] $C$ its **automorphism $\infty$-group** is the [[âˆž-group]] $Hom_C(F,F) \in $ [[âˆžGrpd]] given by the [[derived hom space]] from $X$ to itself. 

For $C$ an ordinary [[category]] this reduces to the ordinary notion of [[automorphism group]].


## Related concepts

There may be the [[stuff, structure, property|structure]] of an [[âˆž-Lie group]] on $Aut(F)$. The corresponding [[âˆž-Lie algebra]] is an [[automorphism âˆž-Lie algebra]].


